<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Set_the_default_route_setting_and_disable_IPv6_information">Set the default route setting and disable IPv6 information</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/PrepareServer&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-14" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/PrepareServer&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-14" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>You must set the default route for the localhost and the default gateway address on all master and worker nodes, and on all NFS servers.<br>
</p>
<ol>
<li>Log on to the node or server and then run the following command to check your default route setting.<br>
<code>grep 127.0.0.1 /etc/hosts</code><br>
If there is no return value, run the following command to set the default route setting.<br>
<code>echo "127.0.0.1 localhost" &gt;&gt; /etc/hosts</code>
</li><li>Open the <code>/etc/hosts</code> files with a supported editor and make sure the IPv6 information has been commented out.<br>
For example:<br>
<pre>#::1         localhost localhost.localdomain localhost6 localhost6.localdomain6 </pre></li>
</ol>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Check_the_default_gateway_setting">Check the default gateway setting</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/PrepareServer&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-15" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/PrepareServer&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-15" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>To check the default gateway address on a node, run the following command on the node:<br>
<code>ip route | grep default</code><br>
If your terminal resembles the following after you run the command, the default gateway address is already set: 
</p>
<pre>default via 192.0.2.1 dev ens32  proto static  metric 100
</pre>
<p>If the default gateway is not set on the node, run the following command on the node to add a default gateway:<br>
<code>route add default gw &lt;<i>IP address</i>&gt; &lt;<i>interface name</i>&gt;</code><br>
For example, you run the following command: <br><code>route add default gw 192.0.2.24 eth0</code>
</p><p><br>
</p>
